<title>ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINK-TO-DELAYED</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-gb">
</head>
<body>
	<h3><i>I delay adding behaviours to the link from me to another.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINK-TO-DELAYED</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for other-end-of-the-link the-other                      
substitute-text-area-for delay-duration delta-t                    
do-after delay-duration
   [add-behaviours-to-link-to list-of-micro-behaviours "Behaviours" [] other-end-of-the-link]</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>Just add micro-behaviours to the list by clicking on the micro-behaviour 
	and navigating back to this page. You can change the expression that 
	specifies who is at the other end of the link. The amount of the delay can 
	also be changed.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>

	<p>

	<a href="ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINK-FROM-DELAYED.html">
	ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINK-FROM-DELAYED</a> 
	add behaviours to the link to another from me. <a href="DO-AFTER.html">DO-AFTER</a> 
	adds behaviours to an agent. <a href="ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINK-TO.html">ADD-BEHAVIOURS-TO-LINK-TO</a> 
	adds the behaviours immediately.</p>
<p>

	Note only some behaviours make sense for a link. For example,
	<a href="SET-COLOR.html">SET-COLOR</a> works fine but
	<a href="SET-SHAPE.html">SET-SHAPE</a> makes no sense.</p>

	<h2>History</h2>
	<p>This was first implemented by Ken Kahn on 6 October 2009. 

</body>
</html>

